cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SI, cs.IT

The paper discusses the use of recurrent neural networks for short-term traffic flow prediction, which is a common application of machine learning and artificial intelligence in the field of transportation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves data analysis and information theory, which could place it in the cs.IT (Information Theory) category. Finally, the paper could also be relevant to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) category, as it deals with traffic management in smart cities.
